
[1]embroil

   EMBROIL', v.t.

   1. To perplex or entangle; to intermix in confusion.

   The christian antiquities at Rome--are embroiled with fable and legend.

   2. To involve in troubles or perplexities; to disturb or distract by
   connection with something else; to throw into confusion or commotion;
   to perplex.

   The royal house embroiled in civil war.
